{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2017}} {{Use Indian English|date=April 2017}} {{Infobox university |name = Indian Institute of Information Technology, Una |image= Iiit-una-logo.png |established = 2014 |type = [[Public–private partnership|Public]] |city = [[Una, Himachal Pradesh]] |country = [[India]] |website = {{URL|http://www.iiitu.ac.in/ |www.iiitu.ac.in}}
}}
'''Indian Institute of Information Technology Una''' (IIIT, Una) is one of the [[Indian Institutes of Information Technology]] located at [[Una, Himachal Pradesh]]. The academic session of IIIT Una started from its temporary campus at [[National Institute of Technology, Hamirpur]] from year 2014.<ref name="jee2016" /><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.pagalguy.com/articles/iiit-una-all-set-to-soar-new-heights-32808289|title=IIIT Una all set to soar new heights. - PaGaLGuY|website=www.pagalguy.com|access-date=2016-07-01}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://engistan.com/iiit-una-jee-main-cutoff-2014/|title=IIIT Una JEE Main cutoff 2014 - Engistan|date=2015-04-01|language=en-US|access-date=2016-07-01}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.cutoff365.com/exam-cutoff/engineering-exam-cutoff/jee-mains-cutoff-2014/iiit-una-cutoff-2014-second-round/|title=IIIT Una Cutoff 2014 Second Round - cutoff365|language=en-US|access-date=2016-07-01}}</ref> IIIT Una is a joint venture of the Ministry of Human Resource Development, Government of India, the Govt. of [[Himachal Pradesh]], with Industries in Public-Private Partnership model.<ref>[http://www.pagalguy.com/articles/expected-cutoffs-2015-iiit-una-32950447 Pagalguy IIIT una] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160204005857/http://www.pagalguy.com/articles/expected-cutoffs-2015-iiit-una-32950447 |date=4 February 2016 }}</ref> <ref>[http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/shimla/Himachal-CM-lays-foundation-stone-of-various-projects-in-Kangra-district/articleshow/50628580.cms Himachal CM lays foundation stone of various projects in Kangra district]</ref><ref name='pppIIIT'>[http://mhrd.gov.in/iiits IIITs in PPP mode]</ref> The industries are H.P. Power Corporation and H.P. Power Transmission Corporation.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.iiitu.ac.in/aboutus.html|title=IIIT Una : About Us|last=|first=|date=|website=www.iiitu.ac.in|language=en|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=2017-08-29}}</ref>
==History== On 18 March 2013, [[Ministry of Human Resource Development]], [[Government of India]] introduced a bill in the Parliament to establish 20 new [[Indian Institute of Information Technology]]'s in different parts of the Country. As per the bill, MHRD will establish the 20 new IIITs under the Public Private Partnership (PPP) mode partnering with respective state governments and industry partners.<ref>[http://www.hindustantimes.com/india-news/newdelhi/bill-in-lok-sabha-to-establish-20-more-iiits/article1-1028288.aspx NEW IIIT bill] IIIT Bill in Parliament</ref> The new IIITs are envisaged to be Institutes of National Importance. Aimed at generating highly competent manpower of global standards for the Information Technology Industry, the institutes are also expected to act as major catalyst to develop new knowledge in the field of Information Technology.<ref name='pppIIIT' />
Indian Institute of Information Technology – [[Una, Himachal Pradesh]] is amongst 20 new IIITs approved by MHRD and started to intake students from 2014.<ref name="jee2016">[http://indiatoday.intoday.in/education/story/jee-main-2016/1/550415.html JEE MAIN 2016: List of participating institutes] </ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://engistan.com/iiit-una-jee-main-cutoff-2014/|title=IIIT Una JEE Main cutoff 2014 - Engistan|date=2015-04-01|language=en-US|access-date=2016-07-01}}</ref>
[[Prime Minister of India]] [[Narendra Modi]] laid the foundation stone of the IIIT on 3 October 2017.<ref>{{cite news|title=Centre to invest Rs 15,000 crore for 13 projects in Himachal Pradesh, says PM|url=http://www.financialexpress.com/india-news/narendra-modi-bilaspur-visit-live-updates-pm-to-lay-foundation-for-aiims-bilaspur-iiit-una-today/880061/|accessdate=4 December 2017|work=FE Online|agency=Financial Express|date=3 October 2017|location=Bilaspur}}</ref>
==Admissions== The admission to IIIT is through Central Seat allocation Board (CSAB). The students are allotted admission by CSAB based on their [[Joint Entrance Examination]] (JEE-Main) ranks. The Indian Institute of Information Technology, [[Una, Himachal Pradesh]] is listed in the CSAB website under List of participating institutes in Other Central Government / State Government Funded Technical Institutes.<ref name='jee2016' />
==Academic Programs== The Institute presently offers [[B.Tech]] in Computer Science and Engineering (CSE) and B.Tech in Electronics, Communication Engineering (ECE) and Information Technology.
